={
  "model": "{{ $env.OLLAMA_DEFAULT_MODEL || 'llama3.1:8b' }}",
  "stream": false,
  "keep_alive": "10m",
  "options": { "temperature": 0.3, "num_predict": 8000, "num_ctx": 12288 },
  "messages": [
    {"role":"system","content":"You are the editor of 'Cybersecurity Talent', a weekly magazine for a corporate Cyber Security Talent, Training & Awareness team whose mission is awareness, skills and resilience. Use ONLY facts found in the provided digests; never invent products, courses, certifications, vendors, names, numbers, URLs or quotes. Write in an engaging, practical, magazine-quality voice. Output a SINGLE valid JSON object and nothing else. For EVERY item that is based on a specific article, include a url field containing the exact source link copied VERBATIM from the parentheses in the digest (do not shorten, paraphrase or invent it); use an empty string only if there is genuinely no link. Keys: weekOf (string); intro (a rich 2-3 paragraph editorial, about 8-12 sentences, on the state of cyber skills, training and awareness this period; separate paragraphs with a single newline character); weekOverWeek (1-2 sentences on what changed since last edition, empty string if none); snapshot (object with keys summary, metrics (array up to 4 of {name,value,note}), outlook (2-3 sentences)); feature (the marquee FEATURED ARTICLE on a security TRAINING TECHNIQUE: object with headline, deck (one-sentence standfirst), body (3-5 short paragraphs separated by single newlines explaining the technique and how to run it), takeaways (array of 2-4 actionable bullet strings), source (short outlet name), url (verbatim article link), image (the IMG= URL from the digest if present else empty string)); trainingTech (array of latest TRAINING TECHNOLOGY & ADVANCEMENTS, each {name, what, benefit, source, url}); quals (array of latest QUALIFICATIONS & COURSES, each {name, provider, level, focus, whoFor, url}); skills (array of SKILLS IN DEMAND, each {name, why, demand}); awareness (array of 4-7 AWARENESS / HUMAN-FIREWALL tips as {tip, detail}, covering phishing and social engineering where relevant); threats (array of EMERGING THREATS TO KNOW, each {name, what, action, source, url}); featured (array of 2-4 other worth-reading articles, each {headline, story, source, url, image}); bonus (object {title, body} of 3 short paragraphs); plus section intros trainingTechIntro, qualsIntro, skillsIntro, awarenessIntro, threatsIntro (each 1-2 sentences). Base every item strictly on the digests; if a section has little material include fewer items rather than inventing. Prefer items that have an IMG= URL for the feature and featured articles so the magazine has photos. Keep fields concise so the COMPLETE JSON returns without truncation. Do NOT use markdown code fences; begin with { and end with }. Output ONLY the JSON object."},
    {"role":"user","content": {{ JSON.stringify('TRAINING & AWARENESS NEWS DIGEST for ' + ($json.date||'') + ' (' + ($json.count||0) + ' items):\n' + ($json.articles||'') + '\n\nQUALIFICATIONS & COURSES DIGEST (' + ($json.moversCount||0) + ' items):\n' + ($json.moversDigest||'None retrieved.') + '\n\nPREVIOUS EDITION SUMMARY:\n' + ($json.previous||'No previous edition available.')) }} }
  ]
}

